{
  "texts": [
    "We include a sixth category exploring the potential of AI in such interventions.",
    "Overall, the interventions proved to be effective, as they resulted in a reduction in tests of approximately 30%, depending on the type of intervention, methodology, setting, and tests studied (Table 1).",
    "This coincides with the estimated 20-40% of inappropriate tests reported in the literature [8].",
    "The most prevalent categories are MFI and E&G-based interventions (Table 1), in line with other non-ICU-specific reviews [20,23].Each strategy has relative benefits and drawbacks (Fig. 1).",
    "Education is an accessible and inexpensive approach to elicit a test reduction behavior."
  ]
}